Dooly looked up from his desk as Konkir entered the room. He leaned back in his chair and watched the frail man close the door.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well?&quot; Dooly asked. &quot;Is the copy prepared?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Dooly,&quot; Konkir said as he sat down across from the gnome. &quot;Everything is ready now.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And? Did you make the changes we discussed?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Dooly. The spell will still function, but not the way it was intended.&quot;  Konkir rubbed his hands nervously.<br>
<br>
&quot;And? Just what exactly will the spell do now?&quot;  Dooly sat up in his chair.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, as we discussed, I re-wrote the second half of the spell to summon a creature without the control. I'm pretty sure it'll work, but I was working from memory of the first spell, so I'm not positive.&quot;<br>
<br>
Dooly rolled his eyes in disgust. &quot;I don't want excuses, I want an explanation.  What exactly will the spell do?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well...&quot; Konkir started.<br>
<br>
&quot;Assuming you've recalled the first part correctly.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well... it should summon a powerful creature, just like it should, but now, if my changes are correct, the summoner won't have control of the creature.&quot;<br>
<br>
Dooly smiled. &quot;And what can we expect a creature will do under these circumstances?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well... it really depends ... I mean, if you summon a beetle or some other non-aggressive creature, then probably nothing. But... if you summon an aggressive creature, for instance a bear, then that creature, the bear, will act as it normally would.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And it will attack the summoner, right?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That's quite possible Dooly, yes.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Excellent Konkir. You've done well.&quot;<br>
<br>
Konkir smiled weakly and looked down at his hands. &quot;Thanks Dooly.&quot;<br>
<br>
Dooly waved his hand casually, and then leaned his elbows on his small desk.  &quot;Now. What about Raff?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you mean?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Can he learn that spell?&quot;<br>
<br>
Konkir shook his head. &quot;I really can't see how he could, Dooly. I mean, he's just barely learned to summon food and water. He only knows the very basics of summoning and he has no idea how to summon elementals.&quot;  Konkir shook his head again. &quot;No, I just can't see it Dooly.&quot;<br>
<br>
Dooly smiled and leaned back in his chair again, placing his hands behind his head. &quot;Good. Anything else to report?&quot; Konkir shook his head. &quot;Good. I'll let you get back to your library then.<br>
<br>
Konkir nodded, stood up and walked out.  Dooly watched him leave and then closed his eyes, a broad smile creeping across his face.  He sighed happily, the sigh of someone who has just completed an important task well. <br>
